verses.text: \w Rejoice|strong="H7442"\w* in the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*, O ye \w righteous|strong="H6662"\w*: \add for\add* \w praise|strong="H8416"\w* is \w comely|strong="H5000"\w* for the \w upright|strong="H3477"\w*.

\w Praise|strong="H3034"\w* the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* with \w harp|strong="H3658"\w*: \w sing|strong="H2167"\w* unto him with the \w psaltery|strong="H5035"\w* \add and\add* an instrument of ten \w strings|strong="H6218"\w*.
\w Sing|strong="H7891"\w* unto him a \w new|strong="H2319"\w* \w song|strong="H7892"\w*; \w play|strong="H5059"\w* \w skilfully|strong="H3190"\w* with a loud \w noise|strong="H8643"\w*.

For the \w word|strong="H1697"\w* of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* \add is\add* \w right|strong="H3477"\w*; and all his \w works|strong="H4639"\w* \add are done\add* in \w truth|strong="H0530"\w*.

He \w loveth|strong="H0157"\w* \w righteousness|strong="H6666"\w* and \w judgment|strong="H4941"\w*: the \w earth|strong="H0776"\w* is \w full|strong="H4390"\w* of the \w goodness|strong="H2617"\w* of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*.\f + \fr 33.5 \ft goodness: or, mercy\f*

By the \w word|strong="H1697"\w* of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* were the \w heavens|strong="H8064"\w* \w made|strong="H6213"\w*; and all the \w host|strong="H6635"\w* of them by the \w breath|strong="H7307"\w* of his \w mouth|strong="H6310"\w*.

He \w gathereth|strong="H3664"\w* the \w waters|strong="H4325"\w* of the \w sea|strong="H3220"\w* together as an \w heap|strong="H5067"\w*: he layeth \w up|strong="H5414"\w* the \w depth|strong="H8415"\w* in \w storehouses|strong="H0214"\w*.

Let all the \w earth|strong="H0776"\w* \w fear|strong="H3372"\w* the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*: let all the \w inhabitants|strong="H3427"\w* of the \w world|strong="H8398"\w* stand in \w awe|strong="H1481"\w* of him.
For he \w spake|strong="H0559"\w*, and it was \add done;\add* he \w commanded|strong="H6680"\w*, and it stood \w fast|strong="H5975"\w*.

The \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* \w bringeth|strong="H6331"\w* the \w counsel|strong="H6098"\w* of the \w heathen|strong="H1471"\w* to \w nought|strong="H6331"\w*: he \w maketh|strong="H5106"\w* the \w devices|strong="H4284"\w* of the \w people|strong="H5971"\w* of none \w effect|strong="H5106"\w*.\f + \fr 33.10 \ft bringeth: Heb. maketh frustrate\f*

The \w counsel|strong="H6098"\w* of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* \w standeth|strong="H5975"\w* for \w ever|strong="H5769"\w*, the \w thoughts|strong="H4284"\w* of his \w heart|strong="H3820"\w* to \w all|strong="H1755"\w* \w generations|strong="H1755"\w*.\f + \fr 33.11 \ft to allâ€¦: Heb. to generation and generation\f*

\w Blessed|strong="H0835"\w* \add is\add* the \w nation|strong="H1471"\w* whose \w God|strong="H0430"\w* \add is\add* the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*; \add and\add* the \w people|strong="H5971"\w* \add whom\add* he hath \w chosen|strong="H0977"\w* for his own \w inheritance|strong="H5159"\w*.
The \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* \w looketh|strong="H5027"\w* from \w heaven|strong="H8064"\w*; he \w beholdeth|strong="H7200"\w* all the \w sons|strong="H1121"\w* of \w men|strong="H0120"\w*.
From the \w place|strong="H4349"\w* of his \w habitation|strong="H3427"\w* he \w looketh|strong="H7688"\w* upon all the \w inhabitants|strong="H3427"\w* of the \w earth|strong="H0776"\w*.
He \w fashioneth|strong="H3335"\w* their \w hearts|strong="H3820"\w* \w alike|strong="H3162"\w*; he \w considereth|strong="H0995"\w* all their \w works|strong="H4639"\w*.

There is no \w king|strong="H4428"\w* \w saved|strong="H3467"\w* by the \w multitude|strong="H7230"\w* of an \w host|strong="H2428"\w*: a mighty \w man|strong="H1368"\w* is not \w delivered|strong="H5337"\w* by \w much|strong="H7230"\w* \w strength|strong="H3581"\w*.

An \w horse|strong="H5483"\w* \add is\add* a vain \w thing|strong="H8267"\w* for \w safety|strong="H8668"\w*: neither shall he \w deliver|strong="H4422"\w* \add any\add* by his \w great|strong="H7230"\w* \w strength|strong="H2428"\w*.

Behold, the \w eye|strong="H5869"\w* of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* \add is\add* upon them that \w fear|strong="H3373"\w* him, upon them that \w hope|strong="H3176"\w* in his \w mercy|strong="H2617"\w*;
To \w deliver|strong="H5337"\w* their \w soul|strong="H5315"\w* from \w death|strong="H4194"\w*, and to keep them \w alive|strong="H2421"\w* in \w famine|strong="H7458"\w*.
Our \w soul|strong="H5315"\w* \w waiteth|strong="H2442"\w* for the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*: he \add is\add* our \w help|strong="H5828"\w* and our \w shield|strong="H4043"\w*.
For our \w heart|strong="H3820"\w* shall \w rejoice|strong="H8055"\w* in him, because we have \w trusted|strong="H0982"\w* in his \w holy|strong="H6944"\w* \w name|strong="H8034"\w*.
Let thy \w mercy|strong="H2617"\w*, O \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*, be upon us, according as we \w hope|strong="H3176"\w* in thee.
